    p Anyway back to the here and now… for us, this summer has been epic! Our #[a(href=pageUrl('clubs/holiday-club.pug')) Holiday Club] and #[a(href=pageUrl('clubs/taningua.pug')) Taningua Clubs] have been more popular and fun than ever, filled with face painting, days at the seaside, water parks, hanging out with pirates at the harbourside and bucketloads of fun in the sun! 
    p Now the team is ready for the ever-popular term-time breakfast and after school clubs to begin again.
    p Our #[a(href=pageUrl('clubs/breakfast-club.pug')) Breakfast Club] is for children who attend Sefton Park and Brunel Fields primary schools, which is held at ‘The Scout Hut’ next door to Sefton Park. Breakfast Club is a great way for children to start the day; in addition to a scrummy, healthy brekkie we provide a variety of toys and games, and encourage creativity and #[a(href=pageUrl('blog/benefits-of-free-play.pug')) free-play] to ease the children into their school day. 
    p Our hugely popular #[a(href=pageUrl('clubs/after-school-club.pug')) After School Clubs] are where children from Sefton Park, Brunel Fields, Fairlawn and Dolphin Schools come to have fun, play and blow away those classroom cobwebs after the school day. We organise craft and cooking activities as well as providing plenty of games, toys, books and sports equipment, and we take a child-led approach whereby children are encouraged to choose how they spend their time. 
    p Please #[a(href=pageUrl('about/registration-booking.pug')) click here] for more information on how to book your children on one of our clubs. 
    p In addition to our day-to-day activities, we’re now busy planning our October half-term Holiday Club. Bookings will open on 26th September, and you can book before 10th October to receive 10% early bird discount.  
